SBS news reporter Ellie Laing has hit back at an article in The Australian that suggested she was hired for her looks . 
  Jim Carroll is the News and Current Affairs Director of SBS . 
  He was criticised for hiring 'good-looking, female, Anglo-Celtic' journalists . 
  The Australian article said he was taking a 'commercial' approach to the network . 
  Laing says she was not hired for looks but for her 'credibility and hard work' She has written an open letter to the article . 
 